<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="365" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 701.6211/452</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Alien Property Custodian</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PAM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 1.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: It has been reported to me as Alien
                            Property Custodian that the German Government owns in the District of
                            Columbia, 51,000 square feet of land of the approximate value of
                            $150,000 situated <pb facs="0422" n="338" xml:id="pg_338"/> on the north
                            side of S Street, between Phelps Place and 23d Street, Northwest.</p>
                        <p>It will be noticed that this property is distinct from the site of the
                            German Legation [<hi rend="italic">Embassy</hi>] and disconnected
                            therewith.</p>
                        <p>I shall appreciate your consideration of this matter, in connection with
                            the former rulings of your Department, and your advice as to whether
                            this property is subject to a proper demand of my office.</p>
                        <p>Yours respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PAM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Mitchell Palmer</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>